summary: Trapped in the Soul Stone
body:
Trapped in the Soul Stone

Peter: *Lying on the floor* Ugh..I am so bored. If we only had something to do here beside stare at the endless ceiling

Karen: We could play “I see something you don’t see” but with people-

Peter: KaREN You’re alive!

Karen: Of course I am. Robots don’t die

Wanda: *scoffs* Tell that to Vision

Bucky: Who’s Karen?

Peter: Karen is the AI that runs my suit Mr. Barnes. Allow me to introduce you. Karen, Mr. Barnes. Mr. Barnes, Karen.

Peter shakes Bucky’s arm

Bucky: A pleasure to meet you… Miss Karen? O_o

Karen: The pleasure is mine James Buchanan Barnes, born on the-

Bucky: O_o

Peter: Karen?

Karen: Yes Peter?

Peter: That’s creepy.

Karen: Ohhh… I understand. It comes off as stalkerish. Dont worry about it Peter. I didnt specifically search for information about Mr. Barnes. I know everything about everyone here.

Peter: That’s not any less concerning.

Karen: Everything for your safety Peter.

Sam: If by “safe”, you mean “dead”

Karen: INSTANT KILL ACTIVATED

Peter: No no no no Karen, it’s a joke. It’s a joke.

summary: Stan Lee remembers Steve Ditko. One thing occurs to me, I really cannot let the week go without commenting on Steve Ditko. Steve...
caption:
Stan Lee remembers Steve Ditko.

One thing occurs to me, I really cannot let the week go without commenting on Steve Ditko. Steve was certainly one of the most important creators in the comic book business and his talent was indescribable. I worked with him for many years and was always impressed with how he saw everything in terms of photos, and pictures, and movement, and scenes. And he just told a story like a fine movie director would. I think he will be very greatly missed by the public, by his fans. And I’m sure there will be a lot written about him as time goes by and I will be one of the guys who buys the first book. You made a real impression here in the world. Excelsior.
